definition.value: A pyrrolizine alkaloid that is produced by a hybrid species of Jacobaea.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 34 carbon atoms and 3 double bonds.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 36 carbon atoms and 3 double bonds.
A pyrrolizine alkaloid that is otosenine in which the hydroxy hydrogen has been replaced by an acetyl group.
A pyrrolizine alkaloid that is onetine in which the hydroxy hydrogen has been replaced by an acetyl group.
An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of chloroacetic acid with the amnio group of 2,6-diethylaniline.
A phosphatidylinositol 34:2 in which the acyl group at C-1 contains 16 carbons and no double bonds while that at C-2 contains 18 carbons and 2 double bonds
An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of chloroacetic acid with the amnio group of 2-ethyl-6-methylaniline.
A pyrrolizine alkaloid that is jacoline in which the 5-methyl group has been replaced by methylene.
A phosphatidylinositol 34:3 in which the acyl group at C-1 contains 16 carbons and no double bonds while that at C-2 contains 18 carbons and 3 double bonds
A phosphatidylinositol 36:3 in which the acyl group at C-1 contains 18 carbons and no double bonds while that at C-2 contains 18 carbons and 3 double bonds
A phosphatidylinositol 36:3 in which the acyl group at C-1 contains 18 carbons and 1 double bond while that at C-2 contains 18 carbons and 2 double bonds
A phosphatidylinositol 36:4 in which both acyl groups contain 18 carbons and 2 double bonds.
A DiHETE that is (5Z,8Z,10E,12E)-icosatetraenoic acid carrying two hydroxy substituents at positions 14 and 15 (the 14R,15S-stereoisomer).
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 36 carbon atoms and 5 double bonds.
A phosphatidylserine 40:5 in which the acyl group at C-1 contains 18 carbons and no double bonds while that at C-2 contains 22 carbons and 5 double bonds.
A triacylglycerol 52:2 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as octadecenoyl, while that at position 3 is hexadecanoyl.
A beta-D-glucan consisting of a poly[(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl] chain attached at position 4 of D-glucono-1,5-lactone via a glycosidic linkage.

A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of homocysteine at the amino group, the carboxy group, or the side-chain amino group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of homocysteine by a heteroatom. The definition normally excludes peptides containing homocysteine residues.

A beta-D-glucan consisting of (1->4)-beta-D-glucan in which the residue at the non-reducing end has undergone formal dehyderogenation resulting on conversion of the hydroxy group at position 4 to the corresponding ketone.
A linear tetrapyrrole anion obtained by deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of mycobilin a; major species at pH 7.3.
A linear tetrapyrrole anion obtained by deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of mycobilin b; major species at pH 7.3.
A linear tetrapyrrole anion obtained by deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of biliverdin beta; major species at pH 7.3.

A linear tetrapyrrole anion obtained by deprotonation of the two carboxy groups and protonation of the imine nitrogen of biliverdin delta; It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A manganese molecular entity with formula MnO2.
A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is obtained from any bacteriochlorophyllide e via deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is obtained from any 7,7-dihydroxybacteriochlorophyllide c via deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A primary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the primary amino function of indol-3-ylmethylamine; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the secondary amino function of 3-(methylaminomethyl)indole; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino function of gramine; major species at pH 7.3.
An  iminium betaine resulting from a transfer of two protons from the carboxy groups to the imino groups of anaerobilin; major species at pH 7.3.

An organic anion that is the conjugate base of 8-amino-8-demethylriboflavin, obtained by removal of the imide proton at position 3. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An isocyanate having a butyl group attached to the nitrogen.

An organic anion that is the conjugate base of 8-demethyl-8-(methylamino)riboflavin, obtained by removal of the imide proton at position 3. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of roseoflavin, obtained by removal of the imide proton at position 3. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A HODE(1-) that is the conjugate base of (9Z,12Z)-11-hydroxyoctadecadienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A HETE anion that is the conjugate base of 7-HETE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A HETE anion that is the conjugate base of 13-HETE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 14-HDoHE(1-) that is the conjugate base of (14R)-HDoHE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 14-HDoHE(1-) that is the conjugate base of (14S)-HDoHE, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An indolylmethyl desulfoglucosinolate in which the C=N double bond has Z configuration.
A hydroxy polyunsaturated fatty acid anion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group of any dihydroxydocosahexaenoic acid.
A dihydroxydocosahexaenoate that is the conjugate base of (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,14S,16Z,19Z)-14,22-dihydroxydocosahexaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A dihydroxydocosahexaenoate that is the conjugate base of (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,14R,16Z,19Z)-14,22-dihydroxydocosahexaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An oxooctadecadienoic acid that is 9,11-octadecadienoic acid in which the oxo group is located at position 13.
A triazolopyrimidine that consists of 1,4-dihydro-7H-[1,2,3]triazolo[4,5-d]pyrimidine bearing an oxo substituent at position 7.
A dihydroxydocosahexaenoate that is the conjugate base of (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,14S,16Z,19Z,21R)-dihydroxydocosahexaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A dihydroxydocosahexaenoate that is the conjugate base of (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,14S,16Z,19Z,21S)-dihydroxydocosahexaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A dihydroxydocosahexaenoate that is the conjugate base of (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,14R,16Z,19Z,21R)-dihydroxydocosahexaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A dihydroxydocosahexaenoate that is the conjugate base of (4Z,7Z,10Z,12E,14R,16Z,19Z,21S)-dihydroxydocosahexaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
